# Playwright E2E Tests (SauceDemo)

End-to-end tests built with Playwright Test + TypeScript for https://www.saucedemo.com.
This project demonstrates a Page Object Model (POM), centralized configuration, and reusable flows.

## Features
- Page Object Model (POM): reusable, typed page actions and selectors
- Centralized config: URLs and user credentials in a single place
- Multi-user coverage: standard, lockedOut, problem, performanceGlitch, error, visual
- Visual checks: HTML report, optional screenshots and video on failure
- CI ready: GitHub Actions workflow

## Folder structure

```
.
├── config.ts                # Shared URLs and test users
├── pages/
│   └── login.ts             # Login page object (LoginPage)
├── tests/
│   └── login.spec.ts        # Scenarios using LoginPage + fixtures/assertions
├── types/
│   └── user.ts              # Shared types for credentials
├── playwright.config.ts     # Playwright Test configuration
├── package.json
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       └── playwright.yml   # CI workflow
├── test-results/            # Generated: raw test artifacts (after runs)
└── playwright-report/       # Generated: HTML report (after runs)
```

## Setup
- Install dependencies: `npm install`
- Install browsers (first run or after updates): `npx playwright install`

## Running tests
- All tests: `npx playwright test`
- Single spec file: `npx playwright test tests/login.spec.ts`
- Single test by title: `npx playwright test -g "Standard user should log in successfully"`
- Specific browser project: `npx playwright test --project=chromium`
- Headed/debug mode: `npx playwright test --headed` or `npx playwright test --debug`
- UI mode: `npx playwright test --ui`
- View HTML report (after a run): `npx playwright show-report`

## Configuration
- File: `playwright.config.ts`
  - testDir: `tests`
  - Projects: `chromium`, `firefox`, `webkit`
  - Reporter: `html`
  - Retries: `2` on CI
  - Trace: `on-first-retry`
  - Screenshots: `only-on-failure`
  - Video: `retain-on-failure`

## Shared test data
- File: `config.ts`
  - `LOGIN_URL` for the SauceDemo login page
  - `users` map for credentials across personas: `standard`, `lockedOut`, `problem`, `performanceGlitch`, `error`, `visual`

## Notes
- No separate build step is required; Playwright runs TypeScript tests directly.
- Linting configuration is not present in this repo.

## Continuous Integration
- Workflow: `.github/workflows/playwright.yml`
  - `npm ci`
  - `npx playwright install --with-deps`
  - `npx playwright test`
  - Uploads the HTML report artifact (`playwright-report`)
